    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>LORETTA ANNOUNCES HONORARY DESIGN STAFF</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20080911.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Staff Writer</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, September 11, 2008</b> &mdash;
    Millsberry&#039;s resident fashion expert, Loretta Rivers, is soaring with creativity these days and with good reason.<br><br>Recently, she held a press conference and fielded questions about the results of her T-shirt design contest.<br><br>In sum: It was a major success. Not only were there more than 15,000 entries, but the 15 lucky designers will finally allow her to attain the coveted haute couture status.<br><br>&quot;This is definitely the high point of my career. I can&#039;t thank everyone enough for all the hard work that went into the entries. The degree of creativity and innovation was astounding.&quot;<br><br>She added: &quot;It certainly proves there are lots of artists in the making in town.&quot;<br> <br>These talented designers were awarded the highest honor Loretta could bestow: the Golden T-shirt.<br>
<br>
&quot;I wanted to give something special to those with the most exceptional designs. And, what&#039;s better than a trophy you can wear&quot;<br><br>&quot;It&#039;s a solid gold T-shirt,&quot; Loretta said, holding up the golden garment. &quot;Just make sure you don&#039;t toss it in with your other laundry!&quot;<br><br>After the press conference, Loretta was swarmed by photographers, fans, and Millsberry fashion enthusiasts. <br><br>Smiling, Loretta thanked the crowd, and said she&#039;d happily stick around to sign autographs and pictures.<br><br>As the admirers lined up, Loretta momentarily surprised the room by returning to the podium for one more announcement:<br><br>&quot;Oh, I almost forgot the most important part.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Starting today, the top 15 T-shirt designs will be available for purchase at Wearhouse. Each shirt has been signed by the artist who created it, so you&quot;ll know exactly who to thank for such incredible work.&quot;<br><br>Today, it seems, beauty is in the eye of the designer. 
    </div>

